node.text:
⁣
⁣
How to Position Players Well⁣
⁣
- Give them a growth environment.⁣
- Recognize each person’s growth needs.⁣
- Open up opportunities for them to grow.⁣
- Walk with them during challenging times.⁣
- Teach them to learn from every experience.⁣
- Help them add value to their teammates.

node.text:
⁣
⁣
If you haven’t read my friend @jefferyhenderson’s new book #FOR I want to encourage you to pick up a copy today. This book is truly perfect for the times we are living in.⁣
⁣
Leaders have never built anything by separating the people.⁣
⁣
You can hear the full conversation @jmarkcole and I had with Jeff on the most recent episode of the #MaxwellPodcast – available on all platforms.

node.text:
I am more passionate than ever that this is our time as leaders to lead! 

From our own growth to our families, our businesses, and our communities – they all depend on strong leadership values and principles. Now is the time to lean in together and build a better and brighter future. We need you!

That is why I am excited to invite YOU to join me and some of my closest friends for our most prestigious leadership and personal growth event of the year – Live2Lead – October 8th in Atlanta, GA.

The lineup of Speakers is a proven group whose heart is built around adding value and guiding you on your leadership journey. We are for you! 

This year’s speakers include:

Ed Mylett - @edmylett 
Jamie Kern Lima - @jamiekernlima 
Valorie Burton - @valorieburton 
Jeff Henderson - @jefferyhenderson 
John Maxwell - @johncmaxwell 

And newly added speakers:

Joel Manby - @joelmanby_official 
Tim Elmore - @growingleaders 
Don Yaeger - @donyaeger 

How do you make your leadership count?

Every one of you, you have a journey to take.
Your first step is your most important step.
You grow with intention.
You don’t go up to the top, you grow up to the top.

“You are ONE decision away from shifting your life from where it is right now to a totally different place” – @edmylett 

“So often our setbacks are setups” – @jamiekernlima 

“What if you interrupted that pattern of thinking and said what do I want that takes your energy and focus off of the problem and begins to focus you on a solution” – @valorieburton 

“Commitment will get you to the starting line. Consistency will get you to the finish line” – @jefferyhenderson 

Join us this YEAR – and be IN THE ROOM on October 8th in Atlanta, GA 
Seating is LIMITED so be sure to secure your tickets today. 

Register through link in Bio.

Live2Lead
One place to hear World-Class Leaders
One place to help you grow in your Leadership
One place to help you transform your life and the world around you.

Success is a series of steps – not one giant leap.
You were born, you were created for your LIFE to count!

Your Friend,

John Maxwell

node.text:
⁣
⁣
Here’s my five-step process for equipping people:⁣
⁣
⁃ Step 1: I do it.⁣
⁃ Step 2: I do it while you watch me.⁣
⁃ Step 3: You do it while I watch you.⁣
⁃ Step 4: You do it.⁣
⁃ Step 5: You do it and somebody is with you.⁣
⁣
When equipping people, most leaders stop at step 4. But the best leaders who have tapped into their multiplication potential, go all the way to step 5.

node.text: In honor of all the fathers today, I wanted to share tip on remembering names. My father impressed upon me at an early age the truth of what Dale Carnegie taught, “The sweetest sound in a person’s ear is the sound of their own name.”

node.text: Leaders listen, leaders learn, and then leaders lead. It’s the listening and the learning that provides the cues of how to lead people. Don’t forget these foundational principles during difficult times. Your people need you to let them know (especially during difficult times) that you understand what they are going through.

node.title: Before I can lead you, I have to connect with you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 24, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'A crisis doesn't make a person; it reveals a person.'.

node.text:
A great leadership lesson from the last 18 months is that when there’s uncertainty on the outside, a leader must have certainty on the inside. Unfortunately, too many leaders are more concerned with the outside than the inside. They’re worried about image instead of integrity—and the difference is revealed more and more each day.

Don’t you think it’s time we change that?

That’s why I want to make sure you’re invited to #Live2Lead 2021 on October 8th in Atlanta, GA. If you’ve never been before, this is our flagship personal growth event. We pull out all the stops for this annual gathering, and what we’ve planned for 2021 is on another level because we believe this is our moment.

Get registered TODAY through the link in my bio!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by John C. Maxwell on August 23, 2021 tagging @jefferyhenderson, @joelmanby09, @valorieburton, @donyaeger, @jamiekernlima, @edmylett, and @tim_elmore. May be an image of phone and text.

node.text:
#GIVEAWAY Alert! Enter for a chance to win a FREE ticket to #Live2Lead 2021!

Last week my team launched virtual ticket sales for Live2Lead. Now, I don’t want you to miss this chance right here – this week only, we are giving away TEN FREE FULL DAY Virtual Tickets to Live2Lead. TEN!

I couldn’t believe it when they told me we were going to do this. I mean, do you understand the value of this full day together? I’ve invited seven of my good friends to join me on stage and help us all grow in business, leadership, marketing, cultural development, and more. And now we are giving tickets away!

Here are the instructions:

1. Follow all speakers: @edmylett , @jamiekernlima , @valorieburton, @jefferyhenderson, @joelmanby_official, @donyaeger, @tim_elmore, @johncmaxwell 
2. Like this post
3. Tag 3 friends who should come to #Live2Lead
4. For an extra entry-Share this post in your story. 

Good luck, my friends!

Winners will be sent DMs 8/31/21

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 22, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Respectis usually gained on difficult ground.'.

node.text:
These three things comprise respect: character + competence + consistency. Notice—all three of these take time to develop.

Always remember, respect is not a personal right. Everyone has the right to speak, but you have to earn the right to be heard.

node.text:
⁣
⁣
How to Position Players Well⁣
⁣
- Give them a growth environment.⁣
- Recognize each person’s growth needs.⁣
- Open up opportunities for them to grow.⁣
- Walk with them during challenging times.⁣
- Teach them to learn from every experience.⁣
- Help them add value to their teammates.

node.text:
I’m thrilled to announce my friend @edmylett will be joining us at #Live2Lead 2021! Get to know a little 
bit more about my friend:

@edmylett decided from a very young age that since he would have to work in life, he might as well work for himself and call his own shots. He realized right away that he was not going to spend his life working for someone else and building their dreams. Today, Ed is one of the premier business leaders, peak performance experts, and motivational speakers in the world. He has a passion for mentoring and coaching others on what it takes to become a champion in all areas of life. He is a bestselling author, host of the top-rated Max Out Your Life Podcast, and speaks all over the world.

Join us LIVE & IN THE ROOM with Ed and many other incredible leaders on October 8th in Atlanta, GA.
Link in bio to register!

node.text:
You’ve heard me say it many times before, people don’t care how much you know until they know how much you care. That’s why you’ve got to find your people before you can lead your people. You’ve got to go where the people are.

My friend @joelmanby_official understands that from his many years of experience leading major companies at the highest level. Tune in to this new episode of the #MaxwellPodcast to learn more from his experience. Available on all platforms today!

node.text:
We have some exciting things to announce about #Live2Lead - our number one leadership event! 

When you purchase the FULL DAY ticket you have the opportunity to hear from EIGHT speakers! This is the largest line up in Live2Lead history! Joining me on the stage this year will be @jamiekernlima @edmylett @jefferyhenderson @valorieburton @joelmanby_official @donyaeger and @tim_elmore!

Not only that, but we are also bringing back the VIRTUAL event with bonus content and interviews with @iamsteveharveytv, @warrickdunn, @angelaahrendts (just to name a few!) in your library immediately, and so much more!  

You don’t want to miss this event. Whether in the room or virtual, there’s a place for you here! For more information go to L2LATL.com. Claim your spot today!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 16, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'The leader's greatest victory IS victory over self.'.

node.text:
We don’t see others as they are, we see others as we are. That’s why the first person we must examine is ourself.

Many problems that leaders have with people are their own problems. Plato said it well, “The first and best victory is to conquer self.”

It’s impossible for an unhealthy leader to have healthy followers.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by John C. Maxwell on August 15, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Practice the Value of Listening Listen with an open mind. Stop what you are doing, make eye contact, and fully engage. Listen objectively. Ask questions. Avoid the temptation to think about what you are going to say next. #TransformationTables CYW'.

node.text:
There is something special about feeling heard. This week, how will you help someone feel heard?

Learn more about #TheValueofListening through Transformation Tables at ChangeYourWorld.com

#TransformationTables #ChangeYourWorld

node.text:
⁣
⁣
If you haven’t read my friend @jefferyhenderson’s new book #FOR I want to encourage you to pick up a copy today. This book is truly perfect for the times we are living in.⁣
⁣
Leaders have never built anything by separating the people.⁣
⁣
You can hear the full conversation @jmarkcole and I had with Jeff on the most recent episode of the #MaxwellPodcast – available on all platforms.
